<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="27" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">
Grasslands in shady, usually deciduous forests and in pastures, margins of alpine wetlands (
<normalizedToken originalValue="“borreguiles”">&quot;borreguiles&quot;</normalizedToken>
) and fissures of rocks; edaphically indifferent; (135) 550-2980 m a.s.l.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="27" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">
Europe, temperate Asia and NW Africa (Morocco); introduced in other parts of the world (e.g. Canada, USA, Patagonia and Guatemala). N half and S third of the Iberian Peninsula. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">And. Por.</emphasis>
: BA DL TM. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Spa.</emphasis>
: (A) (Ab) Al Av B Bu Ca Cc Cs Cu Ge Gr Gu Hu J L Le Lo Lu M (Ma) Na Or O P S Sa Sg So SS T Te To V Va Vi Z Za.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
